subject: [Flagged] 'Job Description'
description:
Knowledge Capture

Flagged from ticket #6205. | Edit article

# Job Description

Jennifer, last edited November 1, 2017

Our Couriers must have a passion for customer service, and a mode of transportation that facilitates delivery of all sizes and weights.

We believe in a healthy work-life balance. While we work very hard at what we do, we also want you to have room for family, friends, and, of course, yourself. We keep sane work hours so that we can pursue our passions outside of the office.

This needs to be updated. Please review.

We also volunteer regularly. Our employees are active in our respective neighborhoods, working to amplify the great qualities that already exist in our local communities.

If you want to be part of our team, To apply, click here.

--

You can't beat a good smoothie! I have everything frozen in a Zip-Lock bag in my freezer and then throw it all in the blender in the morning. Takes no time at all...

- 2 cups spinach
- 2 cups water
- 1 cup mango
- 1 cup pineapple
- 2 bananas

GIVING THANKS FOR LITTLE THINGS

We admit it. We are often on autopilot as we boil the water and measure the grounds for our morning caffeine. But in honor of Thanksgivingand Mr. Peet, who was a little-known follower of Zen practicewe invite you to experiment with being fully present during each seemingly small step of your daily ritual. When done with intention and care, we find they culminate in something even better than just right. Happy Thanksgiving, Peetniks.

subject: [Flagged] 'Can I Pre-Order Food?'
description:
Knowledge Capture

Flagged from ticket #7713. | Edit article

# Can I Pre-Order Food?

Francis Kind - CE, last edited July 18, 2018

Yes. You can pre-order food for your parties, corporate events, or any other events.

You can place orders no later than 48 hours before the delivery time. At the moment, you can only pre-order food by sending an email to orders@eatwell.zendesk.com.

Please note you will be able to change or cancel your order no later than 36 hours before the delivery time.

## Allergens

If you or your guests have food allergies/intolerances, make sure to state it in your order. Our agents will discuss all the options with you before confirming the order.

This needs updating.

description:
Knowledge Capture

Flagged from ticket #7777. | Edit article

# Can I Pre-Order Food?

Francis Kind - CE, last edited July 18, 2018

Yes. You can pre-order food for your parties, corporate events, or any other events.

You can place orders no later than 48 hours before the delivery time. At the moment, you can only pre-order food by sending an email to orders@eatwell.zendesk.com.

Please note you will be able to change or cancel your order no later than 36 hours before the delivery time.

Customer said to incorporate screenshots

## Allergens

If you or your guests have food allergies/intolerances, make sure to state it in your order. Our agents will discuss all the options with you before confirming the order.

# Allergens

Paul Geraghty - CE, last edited December 17, 2018

The food prepared by the restaurant may contain any or all of the following allergens:

Cereals containing gluten

Crustaceans

Eggs

Fish

Peanuts

Soybeans

Milk

Nuts

Contact us using Live Chat or email if you have questions about allergens. Please state clearly to your Eat Well customer care agent that your query is related to allergen information.
